      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) for hemolysis index QoI is below 5% on the medium-fine mesh pair.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study (4.2M, 9.8M, 22.1M cells) yielded GCI of 3.7% for normalized hemolysis index on the medium-fine pair. Richardson extrapolation confirms asymptotic range. Meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions replicated in simulation within documented uncertainty bounds; flow rate and rotational speed match to within 2%.",
      "rationale": "FDA GCBP bench test conditions (flow rates 2.5–6.0 L/min, speeds 2000–3500 RPM) reproduced in CFD with inlet velocity profiles derived from PIV measurements. Boundary condition fidelity confirmed within 1.8%. Meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted hemolysis index values agree with experimental measurements within combined simulation and measurement uncertainty bounds across all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "CFD predictions of normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) show agreement within uncertainty bounds at four of five operating points. At the highest shear condition (6.0 L/min, 3500 RPM), predicted NIH of 0.0041 g/100L exceeds the experimental value of 0.0028 g/100L by 46%, outside the combined expanded uncertainty interval of ±28%. The discrepancy is attributed to transitional flow features near the impeller tip that the k-omega SST model does not fully resolve at this operating point. The team notes this single outlier does not affect the relative hemolysis ranking across operating conditions, which is the primary COU objective. Overall output comparison assessed at level 1, below the required level 2 for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
